body_html:
The bug has been resolved in the master branch, I was using the 0.10rc0 branch. All that's required now for wide_n_deep_tutorial.py to work on Python 3 is the urllib -> urllib.request change mentioned above. With that change on the master branch, you get the same accuracy on Python 3 as Python 2 for "wide_n_deep" model type.

I'd close this, except not sure if there's a way to make the urllib problem work on both Python 2 and 3. Maybe you want to leave this open for that bit of it? Anyway, thanks!
